#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:0.5"
msgid "25. Cīvaraacchindanasikkhāpada"
msgstr "25. The training rule on taking robe-cloth back"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np25.1, pts-vp-en2.139, ms1V_2336
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan said to his brother’s student,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.3"
msgid "“ehāvuso, janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, let’s go wandering in the country.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.4"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, gamissāmi;"
msgstr "“I can’t go, Venerable,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.5"
msgid "dubbalacīvaromhī”ti."
msgstr "my robes are worn.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.6"
msgid "“Ehāvuso, ahaṃ te cīvaraṃ dassāmī”ti"
msgstr "“I’ll give you a robe.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.7"
msgid "tassa cīvaraṃ adāsi."
msgstr "And he gave him a robe."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.8"
msgid "Assosi kho so bhikkhu—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards that monk heard"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.9"
msgid "“bhagavā kira janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti."
msgstr "that the Master was about to go wandering in the country."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho tassa bhikkhuno etadahosi—"
msgstr "He thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.11"
msgid "“na dānāhaṃ āyasmatā upanandena sakyaputtena saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmi, bhagavatā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Now I won’t go wandering with Venerable Upananda, but with the Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.12"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then, when Upananda said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.13"
msgid "“ehi dāni, āvuso, janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Let’s go,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.14"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, bhante, tayā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmi, bhagavatā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "he replied, “I’m not going with you, but with the Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.15"
msgid "“Yampi tyāhaṃ, āvuso, cīvaraṃ adāsiṃ, mayā saddhiṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti,"
msgstr "“Well, the robe I gave you is going with me,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.16"
msgid "kupito anattamano acchindi."
msgstr "and he just took it back in anger."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.17"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "That monk told other monks what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.18"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "And the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.19"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Upananda,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.20"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Upananda give away a robe and then take it back in anger?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli3.255, ms1V_2337
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.21"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.140
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.22"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Upananda, that you acted like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.23"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.24"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.25"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, how can you give a robe to a monk and then take it back in anger?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.26"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.27"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.27a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

# NOTE: _Cīvara_ means both a finished robe and any cloth that can be used to make a robe. Thus I vary my translation depending on the context.
#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_2338
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.28"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindeyya vā acchindāpeyya vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk himself gives robe-cloth to a monk, but then, in anger, takes it back or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.28a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.29"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.30"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.31"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.32"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.33"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2340
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.34"
msgid "Bhikkhussāti"
msgstr "To a monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.35"
msgid "aññassa bhikkhussa."
msgstr "to another monk."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2341
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.36"
msgid "Sāmanti"
msgstr "Himself:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.37"
msgid "sayaṃ datvā."
msgstr "he himself has given it."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2342
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.38"
msgid "Cīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Robe-cloth:"

# NOTE: The six are linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp; see [](Mv.8.3.1).
# NOTE: This means not smaller than 8 by 4 standard (_sugata_) finger-breadths, or 16 by 8 cm; see [](Kkh. 94.4) and BMC I, pp. 565-566.
#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.39"
msgid "channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ."
msgstr "one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2343
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.40"
msgid "Kupito anattamanoti"
msgstr "In anger:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.41"
msgid "anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto."
msgstr "discontent, having hatred, hostile."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2344
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.42"
msgid "Acchindeyyāti"
msgstr "Takes […] back:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.43"
msgid "sayaṃ acchindati, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "if he takes it back himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2345
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.44"
msgid "Acchindāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets […] taken back:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.45"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "if he asks another, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.46"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi acchindati, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "If he only asks once, then even if the other takes back many times, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.47"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe-clot) should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.48"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.49"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.141
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.50"
msgid "“idaṃ me, bhante, cīvaraṃ bhikkhussa sāmaṃ datvā acchinnaṃ nissaggiyaṃ imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "‘Venerables, this robe-cloth which I took back after giving it to a monk is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.51"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.52"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.53"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.53a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2346
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.54"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained and he perceives him as fully ordained, and after giving him robe-cloth, he takes it back in anger or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.55"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, and after giving him robe-cloth, he takes it back in anger or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.56"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī cīvaraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If the other monk is fully ordained, but he perceives him as not fully ordained, and after giving him robe-cloth, he takes it back in anger or gets it taken back, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2347
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.57"
msgid "Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, after giving him another requisite, he takes it back in anger or gets it taken back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.58"
msgid "Anupasampannassa cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ datvā kupito anattamano acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If, after giving robe-cloth or another requisite to a person who is not fully ordained, he takes it back in anger or gets it taken back, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.59"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, but he perceives him as fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.60"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.61"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If the other monk is not fully ordained, and he perceives him as not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.61a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2348
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.62"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.63"
msgid "so vā deti,"
msgstr "if the other monk gives it back;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.64"
msgid "tassa vā vissasanto gaṇhāti,"
msgstr "if he takes it on trust from him;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.65"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.66"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2349
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np25:1.67"
msgid "Cīvaraacchindanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ."
msgstr "The fifth rule, the training rule on taking robe-cloth back, is finished."
